!!!
%html
  %head
    %meta{:charset => "UTF-8"}
    %title="#{content_for?(:title) ? yield(:title) : 'tree'}"
    %meta{:name=>"viewport", :content=>"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"}
    /[if lt IE 9]
      %script{:src=>"http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"}
    %link{:rel=>"shortcut icon", :href=>"/assets/ico/favicon.ico"}
    %link{:rel=>"apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes=>"144x144", :href=>"/assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-144-precomposed.png"}
    %link{:rel=>"apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes=>"114x114", :href=>"/assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-114-precomposed.png"}
    %link{:rel=>"apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :sizes=>"72x72", :href=>"/assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-72-precomposed.png"}
    %link{:rel=>"apple-touch-icon-precomposed", :href=>"/assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-57-precomposed.png"}
    = stylesheet_link_tag    "application", :media => "all"
    = javascript_include_tag "application"
    = csrf_meta_tags

  %body{'data-spy'=>"scroll", 'data-target'=>".subnav", 'data-offset'=>"50"}
    %div{:class=>"navbar navbar-fixed-top"}
      %div{:class=>"navbar-inner"}
        %div{:class=>"container"}
          %a{:class=>"btn btn-navbar", 'data-toggle'=>"collapse", 'data-target'=>".nav-collapse"}
            %span{:class=>"icon-bar"}
            %span{:class=>"icon-bar"}
            %span{:class=>"icon-bar"}
          %a{:class=>"brand", :href=>"/"}="tree"
          %div{:class=>"nav-collapse collapse"}
            %ul{:class=>"nav"}
              %li{:class=>"active"}
                %a{:href=>"/"}="Web App"
              %li{:class=>""}
                %a{:href=>"/help"}="help"
              %li{:class=>""}
                %a{:href=>"/api"}="API"
      %div{:class=>"container"}
        %div{:class=>"inner"}
          = yield
        %div{:id => 'common', :style=>"display:none;"}
          %header{:class=>"jumbotron masthead"}
            %div{:class=>"inner"}
              %h1="知識と友達になる"
              %p="Be friends with knowledge"
              %p{:class=>"download-info"}
                %a{:href=>"http://mindia.jp", :class=>"btn btn-primary btn-large"}="mindia.jp"
                %a{:href=>"http://tw.mindia.jp", :class=>"btn btn-large"}="tw.mindia.jp"
            %div{:class=>"bs-links"}
              %ul{:class=>"quick-links"}
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/pandeiro245"}="@pandeiro245"
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/satoko245"}="@satoko245"
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/tnantoka"}="@tnantoka"
              %ul{:class=>"quick-links"}
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/akikumo_tea"}="@akikumo_tea"
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/gakico_m"}="@gakico_m"
                %li
                  %a{:href=>"http://twitter.com/tamacya_m"}="@tamacya_m"
          %hr.soften
            .marketing
              %h1 Designed for everyone, everywhere.
              %p.marketing-byline Need reasons to love Bootstrap? Look no further.
              .row
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_042_group.png"}
                    %h2 PVを増やす
                    %p Like you, we love building awesome products on the web. We love it so much, we decided to help people just like us do it easier, better, and faster. Bootstrap is built for you.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_079_podium.png"}
                    %h2 コンテンツ数を増やす
                    %p Bootstrap is designed to help people of all skill levels—designer or developer, huge nerd or early beginner. Use it as a complete kit or use to start something more complex.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_163_iphone.png"}
                    %h2 売り上げを増やす
                    %p Originally built with only modern browsers in mind, Bootstrap has evolved to include support for all major browsers (even IE7!) and, with Bootstrap 2, tablets and smartphones, too.
              .row
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_155_show_thumbnails.png"}
                    %h2 人を活かす
                    %p Grid systems aren't everything, but having a durable and flexible one at the core of your work can make development much simpler. Use our built-in grid classes or roll your own.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_214_resize_small.png"}
                    %h2 Responsive design
                    %p With Bootstrap 2, we've gone fully responsive. Our components are scaled according to a range of resolutions and devices to provide a consistent experience, no matter what.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_266_book_open.png"}
                    %h2 Styleguide docs
                    %p Unlike other front-end toolkits, Bootstrap was designed first and foremost as a styleguide to document not only our features, but best practices and living, coded examples.
              / /row
              .row
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_082_roundabout.png"}
                    %h2 Growing library
                    %p Despite being only 10kb (gzipped), Bootstrap is one of the most complete front-end toolkits out there with dozens of fully functional components ready to be put to use.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/glyphicons/glyphicons_009_magic.png"}
                    %h2 Custom jQuery plugins
                    %p What good is an awesome design component without easy-to-use, proper, and extensible interactions? With Bootstrap, you get custom-built jQuery plugins to bring your projects to life.
                .span4
                  %img.bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/less-small.png"}
                    %h2 Built on LESS
                    %p Where vanilla CSS falters, LESS excels. Variables, nesting, operations, and mixins in LESS makes coding CSS faster and more efficient with minimal overhead.
              / /row
              .row
                .span3
                  %img.small-bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/icon-html5.png"}
                    %h3 HTML5
                    %p Built to support new HTML5 elements and syntax.
                .span3
                  %img.small-bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/icon-css3.png"}
                    %h3 CSS3
                    %p Progressively enhanced components for ultimate style.
                .span3
                  %img.small-bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/icon-github.png"}
                    %h3 Open-source
                    %p
                      Built for and maintained by the community via
                      = succeed "." do
                        %a{:href => "https://github.com"} GitHub
                .span3
                  %img.small-bs-icon{:src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/icon-twitter.png"}
                    %h3 Made at Twitter
                    %p
                      Brought to you by an experienced
                      %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/fat"} engineer
                      and
                      = succeed "." do
                        %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/mdo"} designer
              / /row
              %hr.soften
                %h1 Built with Bootstrap.
                %p.marketing-byline
                  For even more sites built with Bootstrap,
                  %a{:href => "http://builtwithbootstrap.tumblr.com/", :target => "_blank"} visit the unofficial Tumblr
                  or
                  = succeed "." do
                    %a{:href => "./examples.html"} browse the examples
                %ul.thumbnails.example-sites
                  %li.span3
                    %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://soundready.fm/", :target => "_blank"}
                      %img{:alt => "SoundReady.fm", :src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/example-sites/soundready.png"}
                  %li.span3
                    %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://kippt.com/", :target => "_blank"}
                      %img{:alt => "Kippt", :src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/example-sites/kippt.png"}
                  %li.span3
                    %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://www.fleetio.com/", :target => "_blank"}
                      %img{:alt => "Fleetio", :src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/example-sites/fleetio.png"}
                  %li.span3
                    %a.thumbnail{:href => "http://www.jshint.com/", :target => "_blank"}
                      %img{:alt => "JS Hint", :src => "http://twitter.github.com/bootstrap/assets/img/example-sites/jshint.png"}
        %footer.footer{:style => "display:none;"}
          %p.pull-right
            %a{:href => "#"} Back to top
          %p
            Designed and built with all the love in the world
            %a{:href => "http://twitter.com/twitter", :target => "_blank"} @twitter
